<p>An internal link to <a href="start">start</a> and one to a <a
href="/some/namespace/page">page</a> target.</p>
<p>A named internal link to <a href="start">the start page</a> guides
the reader.</p>
<p>External links such as <a href="https://example.com">Example</a> and
the bare form <a href="https://example.org">https://example.org</a> both
work, as does an email like <a
href="mailto:user@example.com">user@example.com</a>.</p>
<p>An interwiki shortcut points at <a
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki">Wiki</a> for background
reading.</p>
